<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1841,1896]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">
<typeStatus box="[151,201,1841,1865]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Andre, 1893" authorityName="Andre" authorityYear="1893" box="[294,617,1841,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinifera">
<emphasis box="[294,484,1841,1865]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Mutilla pectinifera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Andre, E." box="[489,617,1841,1865]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="286 - 296" refId="ref16053" refString="Andre, E. (1893) Pour servir a la connaissance des mutilles palearctiques et description de quelques especes nouvelles. Memoirs de la Societe Zoologique de France, 6, 286 - 296." type="journal article" year="1893">André, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<specimenCount box="[628,647,1841,1864]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, by subsequent designation of Bischoff 1921: 585 (junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Radoszkowski, 1879" authorityName="Radoszkowski" authorityYear="1879" box="[227,586,1872,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caeca">
<emphasis box="[227,367,1872,1896]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Mutilla caeca</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Radoszkowski, O." box="[373,586,1872,1896]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="140 - 156" refId="ref19754" refString="Radoszkowski, O. (1879) Les Chrysides et Sphegides du Caucase. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae, 15 (2 - 3), 140 - 156." type="journal article" year="1879">Radoszkowski, 1879</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<specimenCount box="[597,619,1872,1895]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1942,2040]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">
Three species are recognized in this genus: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Radoszkowski, 1879)" baseAuthorityName="Radoszkowski" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[634,992,1942,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caeca">
<emphasis box="[634,732,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">C. caeca</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Radoszkowski, O." box="[746,984,1942,1968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="140 - 156" refId="ref19754" refString="Radoszkowski, O. (1879) Les Chrysides et Sphegides du Caucase. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae, 15 (2 - 3), 140 - 156." type="journal article" year="1879">Radoszkowski, 1879</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, which is widespread in the Palaearctic; 
<taxonomicName authority="(Turner, 1911)" baseAuthorityName="Turner" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[151,451,1978,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Ctenotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="porcella">
<emphasis box="[151,278,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">C. porcella</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Turner, R. E." box="[295,443,1978,2004]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="141 - 154" refId="ref20552" refString="Turner, R. E. (1911) New Hymenoptera from Ceylon. Mutillidae and Scoliidae. Spolia Zeylanica, 7 (27), 141 - 154." type="journal article" year="1911">Turner, 1911</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[524,582,1978,2004]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[641,756,1978,2004]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
; and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lelej, 1992" authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1992" box="[819,1178,1978,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Ctenotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guangdongensis">
<emphasis box="[819,1036,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">C. guangdongensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lelej, A. S." box="[1045,1178,1978,2004]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="281 - 288" refId="ref17998" refString="Lelej, A. S. (1992) Two interesting species of velvet ants from China (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae). Entomofauna, 13 (19), 281 - 288." type="journal article" year="1992">Lelej, 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,2014,2040]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[272,375,2014,2040]" name="Thailand" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Thailand</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
